25|$|The Partition of India {{is one of}} {{the central}} events in the {{collective}} memory in India, Pakistan, and Bangladesh. On his motivation to write Drawing the Line, playwright Howard Brenton said he first became interested in the story of the Radcliffe Line while vacationing in India and <b>hearing</b> <b>stories</b> from people whose families had fled across the new line.|$|R
